I'm going crazy staying at home. I could go out, but I get nervous and unsure whether somewhere is too crowded. It's also raining this weekend. I feel even more trapped than how trapped I usually feel.

I'm waiting for potential work today. The feeling of being on stand-by is the worst. I would do anything to avoid it. Being on call is fucking mentally draining. It's a subscription, and rent, and everything I hate about lingering, drawn-out, indefinite pain.

I feel bad at work because of J. I hate being co-leads, as that sets it up as a competition, which it shouldn't be but it totally is in my mind. The perfect situation would have been if J didn't get fired and was promoted instead and he and J could duke it out as leads and I wouldn't have to deal with any of these feelings. It would be awesome to spectate the power dynamics. It was a super bad decision on M's part to fire J. It's definitely enough to make me want to quit almost every day now. In that other world, I would have likely stayed forever.

I also hate the level where crypto is. It's not bad enough to be interesting and certainly not good; even worse, the low prices now means it'll stick around these bottom levels for even longer. Anything between $50 and $500 is irrevelant to me. I would start paying attention if it's $50. Might not do anything, but would be very tempted and on alert. I won't sell anything at $500, but would maybe start entertaining the idea. It would be break even, which isn't nothing. I'll jump in at $40, no question. $30k left in the emergency fund is acceptable. I'll totally do it. Right? Ok, guess not. Still doubt here. It's on the edge for sure.

Would I sell at $1000? It's at the right level of temptation. I mostly don't want to because it's not ATH, and I want some vindication that I had waited so long and didn't sell until a new ATH.

So the zone extends out. $40 to $1000.

Fantasizing about crypto and money is the only thing I find entertaining right now.

$30. Absolutely. That's just $15,000. $35,000 is a doable full year of e-fund.

$1200? Still not over ATH. Does it make that much of a difference? It's for sure enough to buy a car, more than double the initial investment, which is also psychologically significant for me. There wouldn't be anything left after the car though. I want some buffer. It's going to have to be $1500. It's clear.

$30 to $1500. I don't move within that.

I don't want $50,000 in cash for an emergency fund. Do I? It would feel hella safe. I could maybe do that if I ever have some money left over. $40,000 seems like a lot as it is. I can set $10k aside in a brokerage until ETH hits $30, then sell everything in there, presumably I'll have the $15k by then.

I also want to double my BTC. If ETH hits $30, it may cost another $15k to buy BTC. That'll be an extra luxury.

$30 may take a while to happen. I can keep the $50k, and start saving up again the hard way to buy what I want. I should have a chunk of that by end of the year.

I'm so tempted to read about crypto now. No discipline. It's pointless discipline too, so I don't even get to feel good about depriving myself of crypto news. It makes no difference either way, other than a little masochism. If I look at the price now, just out of boredom, it'll be at some inoperable and irrelevant price like $120 or $80 or some shit like that. I can't do anything with it. The comments will all be the same. I've read them ten times over before. It's always the same thing. So it really ultimately is an unfulfilling thing for me to check prices today. The only thing that would make it worthwhile is if it actually crashed down to $30. That would be crazy. I would scramble to move money around and likely won't get to buy at that price. That defeatism will stay my hand. Plus I still think I'll get fired soon, and counting on not having to make tough decisions for a while on using my emergency fund or not to waste on crypto. Greed will probably take over. 1000 ETH is a lot of ETH. That would have the nice effect of making my fantasies even more alluring. And I would get to spin off fresh fantasies with new more favorable numbers to play around with.

What would I do if I see $30 ETH right now.

I actually like having a big cushy pile of cash. So flexible. It's totally worth the opportunity cost.
